Description: A success event is a metric used to measure when a user completes a specific goal or valuable action on your site. These events represent conversions and are essential for evaluating the performance of your digital properties.
Notes:
*Key Characteristics:
- Goal-based: Events are tracked when users complete key actions aligned with business objectives.
- Used with eVars: Events are typically attributed to eVars to understand which values influenced the conversion.

event52 is unit price times quantity. For instance, If you add one unit of SM-M105 ($100) to cart, event52 will be $100, and event 52 will be $200 if you add two units of SM-M105 at the same time.
